Title: Scattering Amplitudes and the CPT theorem in String Theory
Authors: A. Pasquinucci and K. Roland
Comments: LaTeX2e, 8 pages, talk given at the Conference "Gauge Theories,
  Applied Supersymmetry and Quantum Gravity", London, July 1996
Report-no: IFUM-543/FT, NBI-HE-96-63
\\
  We discuss the role of the CPT transformation in first quantized string
theories, both on the world-sheet and in the space-time. We explicitly show
that the space-time CPT theorem holds for all first-quantized (perturbative)
string theories in a Minkowski background of even dimension $D>2$.
